\cf0 Because The T is located within the 
\f1\b Santa Barbara Airport airspace
\f0\b0 , when flying from VOR to the T, pilots need to confirm that the SBA Control Tower has been notified of flying activities in the mountains.  We do not want to bother the Control tower staff unnecessarily, so first thing first: tune in to 132.650 or 
\f1\b call 805.967.0283
\f0\b0  and listen for the ATIS that refers to gliders flying in the vicinity of the airport. 
\f1\b If there is no mention of gliding activity,
\f0\b0  hop on the Flying Today section of the SBSA chat on Telegram and ask for someone to open the Mountain Window with the airport. A local pilot will call them to let them know and will confirm on the chat that the window has been open for gliders.\
